Threat Hunting > [T2]: Starting and Accessing Elastic Stack and Kibana

In this lesson, we will learn how to start the Elastic Stack on your lab machine and access the Kibana interface.

Start the Elastic Stack on Your Lab Machine

To start the Elastic Stack on your lab machine, follow these steps:

  1. Open a terminal on your lab machine.
  2. Navigate to the elastic-container directory by executing the following command:
    • cd elastic-container/
  1. Start the Elastic Stack by running the following command:
    • ./elastic-container.sh start

This will take a couple of minutes to set up the whole SIEM environment for you. Once the process is complete, you should see a message indicating that the Elastic Stack has started.

 

Access Kibana Interface

Now that the Elastic Stack is running, you can access the Kibana interface through your web browser:

  1. Open Firefox and visit https://127.0.0.1:5601.
  2. If prompted, enter the following username and password:
    • Username: student
    • Password: student

You should now be able to access the Kibana interface.

 

Enable Dark Mode (Optional)

If you prefer using dark mode, follow these steps to enable it in Kibana:

  1. In the global search bar, search for "Kibana advanced settings."
  2. Locate the "Dark Mode" option and enable it.
  3. Click "Save" and reload the page.

You should now see Kibana in dark mode.

In the upcoming lessons, we will learn how to install and enroll Elastic Agents, work with Kibana concepts, create dashboards and visualizations, and more. Stay tuned for more insights into using Elastic SIEM!
